[quote=“CoonHunter, post:15, topic:286521”][quote author=jjones10 link=topic=378929.msg2850091#msg2850091 date=1246488246]
Not Windows INTERNET explorer. windows DESKTOP explorer. When i start the computer, it shows up as a black screen and there is nothing to click on. So i have to go task manager> run> CMD> explorer.exe

It took me like 2 weeks to figure it out
[/quote]

So thats what that stupid thing is that says I ran it. I always wondered how to fix that besides just rebooting.

BTW: Go to run, type in msconfig. Click startup tab. Just find exlorer.exe in that, if not see about adding it. That is where you control all of your startup files.[/quote]
